          • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

            Another impressive win albeit against a clearly poor side comparative to the best, or even 2nd tier, teams at this level. This could realistically have been 8-0 on genuine chances alone and Basel fans wouldn't have been able to complain the score was unfair. Except the idiots in the corner wearing sunglasses obviously. There was a blatant penalty on Walcott in the first half. There must be a new UEFA rule which allows you to take out the player before getting the ball. My guess is it wont be applicable against Barcelona. Walcott was excellent as were Sanchez and Cazorla. Given this game was won at 2-0 because Basel were so hopeless in attack, I would've liked to have seen Perez in the 9 for half an hour. He would've been on the end of at least 2 genuine chances, at the very least scoring 1 or both would've been a confidence boost. It's impossible to criticise anybody except for maybe conversion of chances after the 2nd goal went in. I look forward to meeting City in the league. ;-)

I want to be uncertain of how many goals we'll win by and I think Arsenal is a club that deserves that expectation. And if we 'show-up' today, the latter is the case. Unfortunately the former is what I'll have to go with.
